SIMPLE: salutatory
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salutatory
<hw>Sa*lu"ta*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salutatorius</ets>. See <er>Salute</er>.]</ety> <def>Containing or
expressing salutations; speaking a welcome; greeting; -- applied
especially to the oration which introduces the exercises of the
Commencements, or similar public exhibitions, in American
colleges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salutatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Salutatory
<hw>Sa*lu"ta*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place for
saluting or greeting; a vestibule; a porch.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(American Colleges)</fld> <def>The salutatory
oration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salute</ent>⟦br⟧
